use python in the virtualenv folder
leave the venv file alone
keyword: "which" tells you where the file lives
when venv is running, you use the modules in the venv directory
can move to any other directory when venv is running: useful so that you dont commit the venv directory when using Github
jinja allows you to separate html files and python files



HTML Templates (jinja2)

	Takes a lot of the HTML out of your python code.

	Template files must be stored in a templates/ directory at the same level as your Flask app file.

